                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Varia. Ff. i v(erso)-ii v(erso): Image of Mary, “Greeting to your
                            birth, Our Lady,” Répertoire 23. Incipit: ሰላም፡ ለልደትኪ፡ እግዝእትየ፡ ማርያም፡
                            ቤዛዊተ፡ ኵሉ፡ ዓለም፡. Ff. 1r-49r: Praises of Mary, not arranged for the days
                            of the week, but listed here by their content: Monday (1r), Tuesday
                            (6r), Wednesday (15r), Thursday (25r), Friday (36r), Saturday (41v),
                            Sunday (44v). Ff. 49r-64v: Gate of Light. Ff. 65r-67v: Excerpt from Gate
                            of Light, incomplete at the beginning. Ff. 68r-69v: Introductory words
                            of the Deacon before reading from the Epistles of Paul, and other
                            excerpts, written in red ink. Ff. 70r-85v: Image of the Praises of Mary,
                            Mälk‘a Wǝddase, መልክአ፡ ውዳሴ፡ Répertoire 398; Incipit: ፈቀደ: እግዚእ: ለአዳም:
                            ያግዕዞ: MG 701ff. </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <textLang/>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
